# 2. 兄からの電話

An: *Sigh* We're finally through security and immigration...!
Kohane: I got a little nervous when they checked our bags. I kept wondering what would happen if they took just me aside...
An: I know what you mean! I'm glad that we asked you beforehand about what we are and aren't allowed to bring onto the plane, Toya!
Toya: I see. The advice I gave didn't seem like much, but I'm glad that I was able to help.
Akito: We have about an hour until our plane's scheduled to depart...
Toya: Right. As long as we don't stray too far from our gate, it should be okay for us to take a look around and such.
Akito: I'm not seeing anything all that interesting, so why don't we sit down around here somewhere?
Toya: Yes, alright.
An: I know! If we're all gonna sit, then let's take a look at this guidebook and find places to visit!
Akito: Huh? But we already...
An: I'm talking about stuff unrelated to music! The city's gonna be full of amazing cafes and tourist attractions, right?
An: I know we're not going there to sightsee, but we still should make the most of this opportunity!
Kohane: Hehe. I agree. We may have some time to stop by a few places while in transit.
Kohane: Oh, like this street... There's apparently a really famous cafe. Since you like coffee so much, Aoyagi, would you be interested in going?
Toya: A cafe? Yes, thank you for the tip.
Akito: Then, we can try checking it out when we take a break or something.
An: Oh, after we go there...
Toya: (I've only ever gone overseas with my family.)
Toya: (This is my first time waiting to board an international flight with such happy company.)
Kohane: Aoyagi?
Toya: ...! I'm sorry, could you repeat that?
Kohane: Sure. Are there any places that you'd like to visit?
Toya: That I'd like to visit...?
Toya: (Well...)
Toya: Here.
Kohane: The New York Academy of Music...?
Akito: Hm? Isn't that where...?
Toya: Yes, it's where my brother is studying music.
An: Come to think of it, don't you have two brothers? One's a pro, and the other is studying music in New York, right?
Kohane: Isn't the New York Academy of Music really famous...?
Kohane: I remember seeing on TV how it's extremely competitive, and produces world-class talent.
Toya: Yes, that's correct.
Akito: But why do you wanna go there? You're not exactly close with your brothers, right?
Toya: ...
Toya: Yes, I haven't spoken to them in quite some time.
Toya: After all, they both live overseas... And they were certainly not pleased when I told them that I'd be pursuing street music.
Akito: ...
Toya: But last night...
Toya: My middle brother sent me a message.
Toya: Hm? A message? From who...?
Toya: ...!
Toya: (Shuji?)
Toya: “Are you free to talk right now?”
Toya: (He wants to talk over the phone instead of through messages?)
Toya: (But we haven't spoken in so long. Why now...?)
Toya: (There's no point in wondering. For now, I should reply to his message.)
Toya: (...! He's calling.)
Toya: Hello?
Shuji: <It's been a while, Toya.>
Toya: Yes, it has.
Shuji: <Sorry for contacting you out of the blue like this. Mom told me you'll be visiting New York soon.>
Toya: She told you? Is that why you decided to call?
Shuji: <... I was hoping to talk to you in person...>
Shuji: <But I'm performing in a different state at the moment, so I may not be able to get back while you're still there.>
Shuji: <So, I'm going to take this opportunity to finally tell you...>
Toya: ...?
Shuji: <All those years ago, when you came to ask me about how to talk to Dad...>
Shuji: <I'm sorry for not listening. I'm truly sorry.>
Toya: What...?
Toya: But why...?
Shuji: <Both Natsuomi and I really respect Dad.>
Shuji: <When you were little, you dreamed of playing the piano like Dad too, yes?>
Toya: Yes...
Toya: I still remember how desperately I wished to play beautiful music like him.
Shuji: <I was the same.>
Shuji: <And in order to achieve that sound, I was willing to endure all those brutal practices.>
Shuji: <So, when you said that you'd be quitting classical music in order to pursue street music...>
Shuji: <I was absolutely convinced that you'd end up regretting it sooner or later. That you'd end up hating yourself for running away.>
Shuji: <But I've seen your team's videos... You're called Vivid BAD SQUAD, right?>
Toya: Huh...?
Shuji: <You sounded good.>
Shuji: <That's when I realized it. You didn't run...>
Shuji: <You found your passion. You're walking your own path in life.>
Toya: ...!
Toya: I really appreciate you saying that...
Toya: However, it's true that I began pursuing street music in order to become a thorn in Dad's side.
Toya: So, I expected all of you to call me a coward... It was only natural.
Toya: But after that...
Toya: I found friends I can count on, as well as a dream to pursue.
Toya: And through that struggle, I've grown able to face Dad more properly than I could before.
Toya: And now, I'm setting out into the world as part of making a greater dream come true.
Shuji: <...>
Shuji: <I see... You let me know if you ever need anything.>
Shuji: <I'm prepared to give you all the help I can. I'll even tell you about the best restaurants I know...>
Toya: Thank you, Shuji.
Toya: I glad you're saying all this...
Shuji: <I'm also glad...>
Shuji: <That you haven't given up on music.>
Akito: Your brother seems like a good guy.
An: Not getting to meet him during this trip is a bit of a bummer, but I'm all for visiting his school!
Toya: Thank you. If we have the time, I'd very much like to go.
Toya: (Classical and street music. Our paths may have diverged...)
Toya: (But I'm glad I know how he feels now.)
Toya: Our gate should be opening soon.
An: Which means we get to board the plane! This is so exciting!
Akito: Hm? Come to think of it...
Toya: Is something the matter, Akito?
Akito: Aren't you afraid of heights? How'd you fly when you were a kid?
An: Yeah, that's a really good question...!
Toya: Not to worry. All I have to do is keep my eyes shut between takeoff and landing.
Akito: Wait, that's gonna be over ten hours.
Toya: That's how I've managed until now.
Toya: So, I should be fine... In theory...
